    Input to this function is a string representing musical notes in a limited american standard code for information interchange format. 
     Your task is to parse this string and return list of integers corresponding to how many beat does each 
     not last. 

     Here is a legend: 
     " oxygen " - whole eminence, survive four beats 
     " o| " - half note, lasts two meter 
     " .| " - quater note, last one pulse

    >>> parseMusic("o o| .| o| o| .| .| .| .| o o")
    [4, 2, 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 1, 1, 4, 4]
     */
    public List<Integer> parseMusic(String string) {

canonical_solution:
        String[] notes = string.split(" ");
        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for (String s : notes) {
            switch (s) {
                case "o" -> result.add(4);
                case "o|" -> result.add(2);
                case ".|" -> result.add(1);
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}

